{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo","doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/$volume","doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/Reactive-Dependencies"],["doc:\/\/Silo\/documentation\/Silo"]],"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo","modules":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/Your-First-Data-Source","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Creating-the-Data-Source"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Building-the-Dice-View"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Rolling-Automatically"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}]},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Setting-Up-the-Dice-Service"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Choosing-the-Right-Refresh-Policy"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Adding-a-Second-Dependency"},{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Bridging-Streams-to-SwiftUI"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Building-the-Roll-View","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/Reactive-Dependencies"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"project","metadata":{"role":"project","title":"Reacting to Dice Configuration","category":"Silo","categoryPathComponent":"Silo"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/silo\/reactivedependencies"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[{"kind":"hero","title":"Reacting to Dice Configuration","chapter":"Reactive Dependencies","estimatedTimeInMinutes":30,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Build a configurable dice roller that automatically re-rolls whenever the player changes the dice type or count. You will learn how to declare dependencies, choose the right refresh policy, and wire SwiftUI pickers to reactive streams — resulting in a fully functional application.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Begin from the same pattern as Tutorial 1 — a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceService"},{"type":"text","text":" that rolls a single D6. The fetch is identical; what changes is where the range comes from."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Currently, the range ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1...6"},{"text":" is hardcoded. The objective is to replace it with a value that arrives from an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream<Int>"},{"text":". When that stream emits a new number of sides, the data source re-rolls automatically. Silo calls this upstream stream a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"anchor":"Setting-Up-the-Dice-Service","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"code":"DiceService-01.swift","runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceService.swift"},{"text":". The structure mirrors ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceRoller"},{"text":" from Tutorial 1 — a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DataSource<[Int]>"},{"type":"text","text":" whose fetch returns a single random roll. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[Int]"},{"type":"text","text":" is an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Array"},{"type":"text","text":", so no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"emptyValue"},{"type":"text","text":" is needed."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step"},{"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".eager"},{"text":", Silo re-rolls immediately whenever ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sides"},{"text":" emits, even before any subscriber has appeared on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rolls.values"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"DiceService-02.swift","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Accept a "},{"code":"sides: AsyncStream<Int>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the initialiser. Wrap it with ","type":"text"},{"code":".dependency(.eager)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and pass it to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dataSource()"},{"text":". The fetch closure now receives the current sides value as a parameter — replace the hardcoded ","type":"text"},{"code":"6","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with the stream’s current value.","type":"text"}]}],"media":null,"type":"step"}],"title":"Setting Up the Dice Service"},{"contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".eager"},{"text":" policy re-rolls even when no view is watching, resulting in unnecessary computation. Switch to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".lazy"},{"text":" so re-rolls only happen while an active subscriber is present.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".lazy"},{"type":"text","text":" defers the re-roll rather than dropping it. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sides"},{"text":" emits while no subscriber is present, Silo remembers the pending change and fires the re-roll the moment the first subscriber arrives — results are always current when the view appears.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"anchor":"Choosing-the-Right-Refresh-Policy","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"code":"DiceService-03.swift","runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Change ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dependency(.eager)"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dependency(.lazy)"},{"text":". This single word controls when Silo re-rolls relative to subscriber presence.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step"},{"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Without "},{"code":"clear: true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the previous results remain visible until replaced by the new ones. For a dice type change, this is confusing; for other dependencies, retaining the previous value during the transition may be preferable. This distinction is explored in the next section."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"DiceService-04.swift","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clear: true"},{"text":" to the dependency. When the dice type changes, Silo immediately emits an empty array before the new roll arrives — so the view never shows D6 results while a D20 roll is in flight.","type":"text"}]}],"media":null,"type":"step"}],"title":"Choosing the Right Refresh Policy"},{"title":"Adding a Second Dependency","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" stream so the player can roll multiple dice at once. When either ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sides"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" changes, the service re-rolls. Both values are delivered to the fetch closure simultaneously.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Silo holds the first re-roll until "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"all","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" dependencies have emitted at least once. The fetch closure is always called with a complete, valid set of inputs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" omits ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clear: true"},{"text":". Changing from 2d20 to 3d20 keeps the previous two rolls visible while the new set loads — a less disruptive transition. Changing the dice type (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sides"},{"type":"text","text":") still clears immediately because previous results are irrelevant for a different die."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"stepsSection":[{"caption":[],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add "},{"code":"count: AsyncStream<Int>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" alongside ","type":"text"},{"code":"sides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Pass both to ","type":"text"},{"code":"dataSource()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as separate dependency arguments. The fetch closure now receives both ","type":"text"},{"code":"sides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; use them to produce the full set of rolls.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","runtimePreview":null,"code":"DiceService-05.swift"}],"anchor":"Adding-a-Second-Dependency"},{"anchor":"Bridging-Streams-to-SwiftUI","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceService"},{"type":"text","text":" is driven by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream"},{"type":"text","text":" values, not SwiftUI state. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RollViewModel"},{"type":"text","text":" owns the streams and acts as the bridge: it creates stream\/continuation pairs, initialises "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceService"},{"type":"text","text":" with them, and exposes simple methods for the view to call."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"AsyncStream.makeStream(of:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" returns both the stream (the read-end, passed to ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiceService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and the continuation (the write-end, kept by ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollViewModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"). Calling ","type":"text"},{"code":".yield()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on a continuation pushes a new value into the stream, triggering a re-roll.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Seeding initial values in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init"},{"type":"text","text":" is important: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiceService"},{"type":"text","text":" will not make its first roll until both dependencies have emitted at least once. Yielding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"6"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"type":"text","text":" immediately ensures the first roll happens as soon as the view subscribes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":"Bridging Streams to SwiftUI","stepsSection":[{"type":"step","caption":[],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollViewModel.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncStream.makeStream(of:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to create stream\/continuation pairs for ","type":"text"},{"code":"sides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Initialise ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiceService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with the streams, then immediately yield the starting values so both dependencies emit before the view appears.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"RollViewModel-01.swift","runtimePreview":null},{"media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"selectSides(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"selectCount(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" methods that call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".yield()"},{"type":"text","text":" on the appropriate continuation. Also make "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"service"},{"type":"text","text":" private and expose "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rolls"},{"type":"text","text":" as a computed property and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reroll()"},{"type":"text","text":" as a convenience method — the view has no need to access the service directly."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"RollViewModel-02.swift","type":"step"}]},{"title":"Building the Roll View","contentSection":[{"mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Build the SwiftUI view around ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollViewModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Because ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollViewModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" owns both the streams and the ","type":"text"},{"code":"DiceService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" needs no parameters — ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State private var viewModel = RollViewModel()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is the only initialisation required and the view compiles standalone at every step.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Re-roll button calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"viewModel.reroll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which in turn calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"refresh(clear: true)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on the data source. This is the same pattern from Tutorial 1, now applied alongside automatic dependency-driven re-rolls.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"contentAndMedia"}],"stepsSection":[{"caption":[],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollView.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollViewModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stored in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The view is already fully self-contained and can be previewed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","runtimePreview":"RollView-01.png","code":"RollView-01.swift"},{"caption":[],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" properties for ","type":"text"},{"code":"rolls","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"isRolling","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Subscribe to ","type":"text"},{"code":"viewModel.rolls.valueWithState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"code":".task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Display each die result in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"List","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with a running total, a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ProgressView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" overlay for the initial load, and a Re-roll button pinned to the bottom that calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"viewModel.reroll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","runtimePreview":"RollView-02.png","code":"RollView-02.swift"},{"caption":[],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" properties for ","type":"text"},{"code":"selectedSides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"selectedCount","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Move the rolls into their own ","type":"text"},{"code":"Section","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and add a ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Configuration\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" section above it containing two ","type":"text"},{"code":"Picker","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" rows. Inside a ","type":"text"},{"code":"List","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Picker","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" renders as a tappable row that shows the current value inline — no toolbar is needed. The pickers update SwiftUI state, but do not yet feed into ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollViewModel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the dice configuration does not change until the final step.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","runtimePreview":"RollView-03.png","code":"RollView-03.swift"},{"caption":[],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"code":".onChange","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifiers for ","type":"text"},{"code":"selectedSides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"selectedCount","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that call ","type":"text"},{"code":"viewModel.selectSides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"viewModel.selectCount","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Each call yields a new value into the stream, which triggers an automatic re-roll — completing the SwiftUI picker → continuation → dependency → re-roll loop.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","runtimePreview":"RollView-04.png","code":"RollView-04.swift"}],"anchor":"Building-the-Roll-View"}]},{"kind":"assessments","anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","assessments":[{"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":".eager","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" policy re-rolls as soon as the dependency emits, regardless of subscribers. With ","type":"text"},{"code":".lazy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", no roll happens until a subscriber arrives.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Immediately when the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DataSource"},{"type":"text","text":" is created by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".build()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With ","type":"text"},{"code":".lazy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the first roll is triggered automatically when the first subscriber appears — calling ","type":"text"},{"code":"refresh()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" manually is not required.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first time "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh()"},{"type":"text","text":" is called manually."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":".lazy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" defers the roll until a subscriber is present. If the dependency already emitted before the subscriber arrived, the pending refresh fires immediately when the first subscriber appears.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the first subscriber appears on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"values"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"valueWithState"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With ","type":"text"},{"code":".lazy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" policy, when does the first roll happen?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The data source waits until every dependency has emitted at least once. Even though ","type":"text"},{"code":"sides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ready, ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must emit before the first roll can proceed.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Immediately after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sides"},{"type":"text","text":" emits."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Silo holds the first roll until all dependencies have values. This guarantees the fetch closure always receives a complete, well-defined set of inputs.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" emits its first value, 2 seconds later."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Multiple dependencies work just like a single dependency. Once all have emitted, the data source rolls automatically according to the configured policy.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The roll never happens — you must call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"refresh()"},{"type":"text","text":" manually when using multiple dependencies."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You have two dependencies. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"sides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stream emits immediately; the ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stream takes 2 seconds to emit its first value. When does the first roll happen?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"clear: true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on the ","type":"text"},{"code":"sides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" dependency immediately empties the cached results, so the view transitions to its “empty + refreshing” state and shows a loading indicator. Without ","type":"text"},{"code":"clear: true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" change leaves the previous rolls in place — a less disruptive transition when only the number of dice changes.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Changing dice type shows a loading indicator while new results load; changing dice count keeps the previous rolls visible until new ones arrive."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The loading indicator is driven by ","type":"text"},{"code":"isRefreshing","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", not by ","type":"text"},{"code":"clear: true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"code":"clear: true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" controls whether the previous ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"value"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" is cleared; the source is marked as refreshing for any in-flight fetch regardless."}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both changes show a loading indicator — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clear: true"},{"type":"text","text":" is required for the loading indicator to work at all."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"isRefreshing","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is part of ","type":"text"},{"code":"DataSourceState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and is delivered by the ","type":"text"},{"code":"valueWithState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stream for every in-flight fetch. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"isRolling","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" state property in ","type":"text"},{"code":"RollView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is driven directly by it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Neither change shows a loading indicator — a separate state variable would be required to track that.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"sides","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" uses ","type":"text"},{"code":".dependency(.lazy, clear: true)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" uses ","type":"text"},{"code":".dependency(.lazy)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". What is the visible difference in the UI when the player changes dice type versus changing dice count?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"DiceService-03.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"DiceService.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","","@MainActor","class DiceService {","    let rolls: DataSource<[Int]>","","    init(sides: AsyncStream<Int>) {","        \/\/ .lazy: only re-rolls while the view is on screen","        rolls = dataSource(sides.dependency(.lazy)) { sides in","            [Int.random(in: 1...sides)]","        } onError: { _ in","            .keep","        }","        .build()","    }","}"],"highlights":[],"identifier":"DiceService-03.swift"},"RollView-02.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"RollView.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","import SwiftUI","","struct RollView: View {","    @State private var viewModel = RollViewModel()","","    @State private var rolls: [Int] = []","    @State private var isRolling = false","","    var body: some View {","        List {","            ForEach(rolls.indices, id: \\.self) { i in","                Text(\"Die \\(i + 1): \\(rolls[i])\")","                    .font(.title2)","            }","            if rolls.count > 1 {","                Text(\"Total: \\(rolls.reduce(0, +))\")","                    .font(.headline)","                    .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","            }","        }","        .overlay {","            if isRolling && rolls.isEmpty {","                ProgressView(\"Rolling…\")","            }","        }","        .safeAreaInset(edge: .bottom) {","            Button(\"Re-roll\") {","                Task { try? await viewModel.reroll() }","            }","            .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)","            .padding()","        }","        .task {","            for await snapshot in viewModel.rolls.valueWithState {","                rolls = snapshot.value","                isRolling = snapshot.state.isRefreshing","            }","        }","    }","}"],"highlights":[{"line":7},{"line":8},{"line":9},{"line":11},{"line":12},{"line":13},{"line":14},{"line":15},{"line":16},{"line":17},{"line":18},{"line":19},{"line":20},{"line":21},{"line":22},{"line":23},{"line":24},{"line":25},{"line":26},{"line":27},{"line":28},{"line":29},{"line":30},{"line":31},{"line":32},{"line":33},{"line":34},{"line":35},{"line":36},{"line":37},{"line":38},{"line":39}],"identifier":"RollView-02.swift"},"RollView-04.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"RollView.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","import SwiftUI","","struct RollView: View {","    @State private var viewModel = RollViewModel()","","    @State private var rolls: [Int] = []","    @State private var isRolling = false","    @State private var selectedSides = 6","    @State private var selectedCount = 1","","    let sideOptions = [4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 20, 100]","    let countOptions = Array(1...6)","","    var body: some View {","        List {","            Section(\"Configuration\") {","                Picker(\"Sides\", selection: $selectedSides) {","                    ForEach(sideOptions, id: \\.self) { Text(\"D\\($0)\") }","                }","                Picker(\"Count\", selection: $selectedCount) {","                    ForEach(countOptions, id: \\.self) { Text(\"\\($0)\") }","                }","            }","            Section {","                ForEach(rolls.indices, id: \\.self) { i in","                    Text(\"Die \\(i + 1): \\(rolls[i])\")","                        .font(.title2)","                }","                if rolls.count > 1 {","                    Text(\"Total: \\(rolls.reduce(0, +))\")","                        .font(.headline)","                        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","                }","            }","        }","        .overlay {","            if isRolling && rolls.isEmpty {","                ProgressView(\"Rolling…\")","            }","        }","        .safeAreaInset(edge: .bottom) {","            Button(\"Re-roll\") {","                Task { try? await viewModel.reroll() }","            }","            .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)","            .padding()","        }","        .onChange(of: selectedSides) { _, newValue in","            viewModel.selectSides(newValue)","        }","        .onChange(of: selectedCount) { _, newValue in","            viewModel.selectCount(newValue)","        }","        .task {","            for await snapshot in viewModel.rolls.valueWithState {","                rolls = snapshot.value","                isRolling = snapshot.state.isRefreshing","            }","        }","    }","}"],"highlights":[{"line":49},{"line":50},{"line":51},{"line":52},{"line":53},{"line":54}],"identifier":"RollView-04.swift"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/ReactiveDependencies#Choosing-the-Right-Refresh-Policy":{"type":"section","abstract":[{"text":"Build a configurable dice roller that automatically re-rolls whenever the player changes the dice type or count. You will learn how to declare dependencies, choose the right refresh policy, and wire SwiftUI pickers to reactive streams — resulting in a fully functional application.","type":"text"}],"role":"pseudoSymbol","kind":"section","title":"Choosing the Right Refresh Policy","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Choosing-the-Right-Refresh-Policy","url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/reactivedependencies#Choosing-the-Right-Refresh-Policy"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/BuildingAD6DiceRoller":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In this tutorial, you will build a D6 dice roller using Silo. The fetch is a single line — "},{"code":"Int.random(in: 1...6)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — so every concept you encounter is focused on Silo, with no boilerplate distractions."}],"role":"project","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"15min","url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/buildingad6diceroller","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller","title":"Rolling a D6"},"DiceService-04.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"DiceService.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","","@MainActor","class DiceService {","    let rolls: DataSource<[Int]>","","    init(sides: AsyncStream<Int>) {","        \/\/ clear: true: empties results immediately on dice type change","        rolls = dataSource(sides.dependency(.lazy, clear: true)) { sides in","            [Int.random(in: 1...sides)]","        } onError: { _ in","            .keep","        }","        .build()","    }","}"],"highlights":[{"line":8},{"line":9}],"identifier":"DiceService-04.swift"},"RollView-04.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/Silo\/RollView-04.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"RollView-04.png","alt":"Roll view showing four D12 results with a total, and the Configuration section showing D12 and 4 selected","type":"image"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Check-Your-Understanding":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Check Your Understanding","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/buildingad6diceroller#Check-Your-Understanding","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Check-Your-Understanding","title":"Check Your Understanding","type":"link"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/ReactiveDependencies":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Build a configurable dice roller that automatically re-rolls whenever the player changes the dice type or count. You will learn how to declare dependencies, choose the right refresh policy, and wire SwiftUI pickers to reactive streams — resulting in a fully functional application.","type":"text"}],"role":"project","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"30min","url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/reactivedependencies","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies","title":"Reacting to Dice Configuration"},"RollView-01.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/Silo\/RollView-01.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"RollView-01.png","alt":"Placeholder view showing the text 'Dice Roller'","type":"image"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/ReactiveDependencies#Check-Your-Understanding":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Check Your Understanding","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/reactivedependencies#Check-Your-Understanding","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Check-Your-Understanding","title":"Check Your Understanding","type":"link"},"RollViewModel-01.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"RollViewModel.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","","@MainActor","final class RollViewModel {","    let service: DiceService","","    private let sidesContinuation: AsyncStream<Int>.Continuation","    private let countContinuation: AsyncStream<Int>.Continuation","","    init() {","        let (sidesStream, sidesCont) = AsyncStream.makeStream(of: Int.self)","        let (countStream, countCont) = AsyncStream.makeStream(of: Int.self)","        sidesContinuation = sidesCont","        countContinuation = countCont","        service = DiceService(sides: sidesStream, count: countStream)","        \/\/ Seed initial values so both dependencies emit before the view subscribes","        sidesCont.yield(6)","        countCont.yield(1)","    }","}"],"highlights":[],"identifier":"RollViewModel-01.swift"},"DiceService-05.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"DiceService.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","","@MainActor","class DiceService {","    let rolls: DataSource<[Int]>","","    init(sides: AsyncStream<Int>, count: AsyncStream<Int>) {","        rolls = dataSource(","            sides.dependency(.lazy, clear: true),  \/\/ new dice type → clear immediately","            count.dependency(.lazy)  \/\/ new count → keep showing previous rolls","        ) { sides, count in","            (0..<count).map { _ in Int.random(in: 1...sides) }","        } onError: { _ in","            .keep","        }","        .build()","    }","}"],"highlights":[],"identifier":"DiceService-05.swift"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/ReactiveDependencies#Setting-Up-the-Dice-Service":{"type":"section","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build a configurable dice roller that automatically re-rolls whenever the player changes the dice type or count. You will learn how to declare dependencies, choose the right refresh policy, and wire SwiftUI pickers to reactive streams — resulting in a fully functional application."}],"role":"pseudoSymbol","kind":"section","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Setting-Up-the-Dice-Service","url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/reactivedependencies#Setting-Up-the-Dice-Service","title":"Setting Up the Dice Service"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/ReactiveDependencies#Bridging-Streams-to-SwiftUI":{"type":"section","abstract":[{"text":"Build a configurable dice roller that automatically re-rolls whenever the player changes the dice type or count. You will learn how to declare dependencies, choose the right refresh policy, and wire SwiftUI pickers to reactive streams — resulting in a fully functional application.","type":"text"}],"role":"pseudoSymbol","kind":"section","title":"Bridging Streams to SwiftUI","url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/reactivedependencies#Bridging-Streams-to-SwiftUI","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Bridging-Streams-to-SwiftUI"},"RollViewModel-02.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"RollViewModel.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","","@MainActor","final class RollViewModel {","    var rolls: DataSource<[Int]> { service.rolls }","","    private let service: DiceService","    private let sidesContinuation: AsyncStream<Int>.Continuation","    private let countContinuation: AsyncStream<Int>.Continuation","","    init() {","        let (sidesStream, sidesCont) = AsyncStream.makeStream(of: Int.self)","        let (countStream, countCont) = AsyncStream.makeStream(of: Int.self)","        sidesContinuation = sidesCont","        countContinuation = countCont","        service = DiceService(sides: sidesStream, count: countStream)","        sidesCont.yield(6)","        countCont.yield(1)","    }","","    func selectSides(_ sides: Int) {","        sidesContinuation.yield(sides)","    }","","    func selectCount(_ count: Int) {","        countContinuation.yield(count)","    }","","    func reroll() async throws {","        try await service.rolls.refresh(clear: true)","    }","}"],"highlights":[{"line":5},{"line":7},{"line":20},{"line":21},{"line":22},{"line":23},{"line":24},{"line":25},{"line":26},{"line":27},{"line":28},{"line":29},{"line":30},{"line":31}],"identifier":"RollViewModel-02.swift"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/ReactiveDependencies#Adding-a-Second-Dependency":{"type":"section","abstract":[{"text":"Build a configurable dice roller that automatically re-rolls whenever the player changes the dice type or count. You will learn how to declare dependencies, choose the right refresh policy, and wire SwiftUI pickers to reactive streams — resulting in a fully functional application.","type":"text"}],"role":"pseudoSymbol","kind":"section","identifier":"doc:\/\/Silo\/tutorials\/Silo\/ReactiveDependencies#Adding-a-Second-Dependency","url":"\/tutorials\/silo\/reactivedependencies#Adding-a-Second-Dependency","title":"Adding a Second Dependency"},"DiceService-01.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"DiceService.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","","@MainActor","class DiceService {","    let rolls: DataSource<[Int]>","","    init() {","        rolls = dataSource {","            [Int.random(in: 1...6)]","        } onError: { _ in","            .keep","        }","        .build()","    }","}"],"highlights":[],"identifier":"DiceService-01.swift"},"RollView-03.swift":{"type":"file","fileType":"swift","fileName":"RollView.swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Silo","import SwiftUI","","struct RollView: View {","    @State private var viewModel = RollViewModel()","","    @State private var rolls: [Int] = []","    @State private var isRolling = false","    @State private var selectedSides = 6","    @State private var selectedCount = 1","","    let sideOptions = [4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 20, 100]","    let countOptions = Array(1...6)","","    var body: some View {","        List {","            Section(\"Configuration\") {","                Picker(\"Sides\", selection: $selectedSides) {","                    ForEach(sideOptions, id: \\.self) { Text(\"D\\($0)\") }","                }","                Picker(\"Count\", selection: $selectedCount) {","                    ForEach(countOptions, id: \\.self) { Text(\"\\($0)\") }","                }","            }","            Section {","                ForEach(rolls.indices, id: \\.self) { i in","                    Text(\"Die \\(i + 1): \\(rolls[i])\")","                        .font(.title2)","                }","                if rolls.count > 1 {","                    Text(\"Total: \\(rolls.reduce(0, +))\")","                        .font(.headline)","                        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","                }","            }","        }","        .overlay {","            if isRolling && rolls.isEmpty {","                ProgressView(\"Rolling…\")","            }","        }","        .safeAreaInset(edge: .bottom) {","            Button(\"Re-roll\") {","                Task { try? await viewModel.reroll() }","            }","            .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)","            .padding()","        }","        .task {","            for await snapshot in viewModel.rolls.valueWithState {","                rolls = snapshot.value","                isRolling = snapshot.state.isRefreshing","            }","        }","    }","}"],"highlights":[{"line":9},{"line":10},{"line":12},{"line":13},{"line":14},{"line":17},{"line":18},{"line":19},{"line":20},{"line":21},{"line":22},{"line":23},{"line":25},{"line":26},{"line":27},{"line":28},{"line":29},{"line":30},{"line":31},{"line":32},{"line":33},{"line":34}],"identifier":"RollView-03.swift"},"doc://Silo/tutorials/Silo/BuildingAD6DiceRoller#Creating-the-Data-Source":{"type":"section","abstract":[{"text":"In this tutorial, you will build a D6 dice roller using Silo. The fetch is a single line — ","type":"text"},{"